File: Amy'Leigh de Jager was taken outside her school earlier this month. JOHANNESBURG - The fourth suspect in the Amy’Leigh de Jager kidnapping case has appeared in the Vanderbijlpark Magistrate’s Court. The six-year-old girl was taken outside her school earlier this month. The abduction was allegedly masterminded by a teacher. READ: Amy'Leigh kidnapped to 'save suspect's daughter' On Monday, 24-year-old Bofokeng Molemohi was arrested on charges of kidnapping and extortion. It's not clear what role he played. Molemohi is remaining in custody until more personal details can be obtained. He’ll be back in court on 2 October 2019.